                <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
                <p class="last-updated">Last updated: February 7, 2026</p>
            </div>

            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>Ember Labs ("we," "our," or "us") operates Allergy Sentinel (the "App"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application.</p>
            <p>We are committed to protecting your privacy. Allergy Sentinel is designed with a privacy-first architecture, processing the vast majority of data directly on your device.</p>
            <p>Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.</p>

            <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
            <p><strong>Information You Provide Directly</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Allergy profile information (allergen sensitivities, severity levels)</li>
                <li>Symptom logs and health tracking data you choose to record</li>
                <li>Account information if you create an account (email address)</li>
                <li>Feedback and support communications</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>Information Collected Automatically</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Location data (with your permission) to provide hyperlocal pollen and air quality information</li>
                <li>Device information (device type, operating system version)</li>
                <li>App usage analytics (features used, session duration)</li>
                <li>Crash reports and performance data</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>Information from Third-Party Services</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Pollen data from environmental data providers (Breezometer, Google Pollen API)</li>
                <li>Air quality data from environmental monitoring services</li>
                <li>Weather data from weather service providers</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Provide personalized pollen and air quality alerts based on your location and allergy profile</li>
                <li>Display real-time environmental conditions in your neighborhood</li>
                <li>Calculate safe commute routes with lower allergen exposure</li>
                <li>Track and analyze your symptom patterns over time</li>
                <li>Send push notifications about pollen spikes and fresh air opportunities</li>
                <li>Improve and optimize the App's features and user experience</li>
                <li>Respond to your support requests and communications</li>
                <li>Process subscription payments through Apple's App Store</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>On-Device Processing</h2>
            <p>Allergy Sentinel is built with privacy at its core. The following data is processed and stored entirely on your device and is never transmitted to our servers:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Your allergy profile and sensitivity settings</li>
                <li>Symptom logs and health tracking history</li>
                <li>Personal preferences and app settings</li>
                <li>Historical trends and pattern analysis</li>
                <li>Cached environmental data</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Location data is used only to fetch relevant environmental data for your area and is not stored on our servers or shared with third parties for tracking purposes.</p>

            <h2>Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
            <p>We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share information only in the following circumstances:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> We use third-party APIs (Breezometer, Google) to fetch environmental data. These services receive only your approximate location to provide relevant data.</li>
                <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> We use privacy-focused analytics to understand app usage patterns. This data is aggregated and anonymized.</li>
                <li><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong> We may disclose information if required by law, court order, or government regulation.</li>
                <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, user information may be transferred as part of that transaction.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Data Retention</h2>
            <p>Data stored on your device remains there until you delete the App or clear its data. We retain server-side data (if any) only as long as necessary to provide our services:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Account information: Retained until you delete your account</li>
                <li>Support communications: Retained for up to 2 years</li>
                <li>Analytics data: Aggregated and anonymized, retained indefinitely</li>
                <li>Subscription records: Managed by Apple through App Store</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Your Rights and Choices</h2>
            <p>You have the following rights regarding your data:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
                <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate personal data</li>
                <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Request deletion of your personal data</li>
                <li><strong>Portability:</strong> Request your data in a portable format</li>
                <li><strong>Withdraw Consent:</strong> Disable location services or notifications at any time through your device settings</li>
                <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> Unsubscribe from marketing communications</li>
            </ul>
            <p>To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at <a href="mailto:support@emberlabs.com">support@emberlabs.com</a>.</p>

            <h2>Location Data</h2>
            <p>Allergy Sentinel requests access to your device's location to provide hyperlocal pollen and air quality information. You can control location access through your device settings:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>While Using the App:</strong> Location is accessed only when the app is open</li>
                <li><strong>Always:</strong> Enables background location for proactive alerts (optional)</li>
                <li><strong>Never:</strong> Disables location features; you can still use the app with manual location entry</li>
            </ul>
            <p>We request location data at 1km precision to balance accuracy with privacy. Your exact address is never stored or transmitted.</p>

            <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>Allergy Sentinel is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us at <a href="mailto:support@emberlabs.com">support@emberlabs.com</a> so we can delete such information.</p>

            <h2>Security</h2>
            <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information, including:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Encryption of data in transit using TLS/SSL</li>
                <li>On-device encryption for locally stored data</li>
                <li>Secure API communications with third-party services</li>
                <li>Regular security assessments and updates</li>
            </ul>
            <p>However, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.</p>

            <h2>International Users</h2>
            <p>Allergy Sentinel is operated from the United States. If you are accessing the App from outside the United States, please be aware that your information may be transferred to, stored, and processed in the United States where our servers are located.</p>
            <p>By using the App, you consent to the transfer of your information to the United States and the use and disclosure of your information as described in this Privacy Policy.</p>

            <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy in the App and updating the "Last updated" date.</p>
            <p>You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Changes are effective immediately upon posting.</p>

            <h2>Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us:</p>
